00:32:03.290 --> 00:32:05.803
Now, with this in
mind and realizing

00:32:05.803 --> 00:32:07.970
that private sector can't
solve this for the reasons

00:32:07.970 --> 00:32:11.180
we talked about, let's
talk about the role--

00:32:11.180 --> 00:32:14.531
let's talk about the
role of government,

00:32:14.531 --> 00:32:18.300
government solutions.

00:32:18.300 --> 00:32:20.120
So, once again,
remember the basic logic

00:32:20.120 --> 00:32:23.180
of this class, which is that--

00:32:23.180 --> 00:32:28.650
the basic logic of the
class, which is that if--

00:32:28.650 --> 00:32:31.670
the basic logic of the class
is that the market knows best

00:32:31.670 --> 00:32:33.072
unless there's a market failure.

00:32:33.072 --> 00:32:35.030
If there's a market
failure, the private market

00:32:35.030 --> 00:32:36.470
will deliver a deadweight loss.

00:32:36.470 --> 00:32:38.720
Now we have to ask can the
government actually make it

00:32:38.720 --> 00:32:39.260
better.

00:32:39.260 --> 00:32:41.177
Remember, we talked about
monopoly regulation.

00:32:41.177 --> 00:32:44.743
The government may or may
not make it better, OK?

00:32:44.743 --> 00:32:47.160
Information asymmetries, it
may or may not make it better.

00:32:47.160 --> 00:32:48.320
Same thing with
externalities, the government

00:32:48.320 --> 00:32:49.130
may not make it better.

00:32:49.130 --> 00:32:51.213
So let's talk about how
the government, in theory,

00:32:51.213 --> 00:32:52.658
could make it better, OK?

00:32:52.658 --> 00:32:54.200
Well, there's two
ways the government

00:32:54.200 --> 00:32:55.460
could make it better.

00:32:55.460 --> 00:32:58.100
One way is by regulation.

00:32:58.100 --> 00:33:03.350
So go back to figure 22-1, OK?

00:33:03.350 --> 00:33:05.480
The government could
literally regulate

00:33:05.480 --> 00:33:08.240
and could say, look, we know
the optimal level of steel

00:33:08.240 --> 00:33:10.290
to be produced is Q2.

00:33:10.290 --> 00:33:12.740
We're just going to
tell you to produce Q2.

00:33:12.740 --> 00:33:13.670
That's it.

00:33:13.670 --> 00:33:15.770
Problem solved, OK?

00:33:15.770 --> 00:33:18.290
We just say, hey, steel plant,
we know the optimum is Q2.

00:33:18.290 --> 00:33:19.010
You produce Q2.

00:33:19.010 --> 00:33:20.690
Problem solved.

00:33:20.690 --> 00:33:23.180
The problem with that is
that requires the government

00:33:23.180 --> 00:33:24.980
to know quite a lot.

00:33:24.980 --> 00:33:26.900
The government needs
to know both the supply

00:33:26.900 --> 00:33:31.310
and the demand curves to
figure out where Q2 is

00:33:31.310 --> 00:33:33.560
and what they should regulate.

00:33:33.560 --> 00:33:36.462
Let's say all the government
knows is the damage being done,

00:33:36.462 --> 00:33:37.920
and let's say the
damage is linear,

00:33:37.920 --> 00:33:40.550
or they can approximate
it as linear.

00:33:40.550 --> 00:33:43.390
Then there's a much
easier solution,

00:33:43.390 --> 00:33:46.213
which is a corrective tax.

00:33:46.213 --> 00:33:47.880
What if the government
came in and said,

00:33:47.880 --> 00:33:50.217
look, I don't where demand
and supply curves are?

00:33:50.217 --> 00:33:51.050
I don't really know.

00:33:51.050 --> 00:33:52.467
It's really hard
to figure it out.

00:33:52.467 --> 00:33:56.035
All I know is that, for every
unit of steel you produce,

00:33:56.035 --> 00:33:57.410
which is a unit
of sludge, you're

00:33:57.410 --> 00:34:00.348
killing $100 worth of fish.

00:34:00.348 --> 00:34:01.140
That's what I know.

00:34:01.140 --> 00:34:05.170
That I can study
environmentally, OK?

00:34:05.170 --> 00:34:08.040
What if I simply
tax the steel plant

00:34:08.040 --> 00:34:10.830
by $100 for every unit
of steel they produced?

00:34:10.830 --> 00:34:13.389
That is, if I imposed a
tax on the steel plant--

00:34:13.389 --> 00:34:14.763
STUDENT: Don't you mean sludge?

00:34:14.763 --> 00:34:16.180
JONATHAN GRUBER:
One unit of steel

00:34:16.180 --> 00:34:18.190
is one unit of sludge
in this example.

00:34:18.190 --> 00:34:21.520
So I'm going to tax every
unit of steel they produce,

00:34:21.520 --> 00:34:24.880
which is the same as producing
